FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FIn Wales, Plaid Cymru and Reform are
OL,7,Fnow battling it out in opinion polls
OL,8,Ffor first place. In Scotland, the SNP
OL,9,Fremains in the lead despite losing
OL,10,Fsupport, while Reform and Labour are
OL,11,Ffighting for second place. In England,
OL,12,FReform top the polls but the Greens,
OL,13,FLiberal Democrats, Labour and
OL,14,FConservatives are effectively now neck
OL,15,Fand neck.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FThis can't only be down to the choices
OL,7,Fof these challenger parties. Labour is
OL,8,Flosing voters because of their
OL,9,Fgoverning record and our financial
OL,10,Fworries. The Conservatives continue to
OL,11,Fbe punished for their time in office,
OL,12,Ftoo.
OL,14,FBut is this a peak moment of protest,
OL,15,For are we seeing the beginning of the
OL,16,Fend for the two traditional parties of
OL,17,Fgovernment?
OL,19,FWhile fragmentation follows a longer-
OL,20,Fterm trend, we've never seen this much
OL,21,Ffragmentation in vote intention.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
