OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FITV News has been given exclusive data
OL,7,Ffrom YouGov, showing people switching
OL,8,Fbetween parties (from their July 2024
OL,9,Fvote and their current vote
OL,10,Fintention). Just look at the following
OL,11,Fflows. We're seeing switching like
OL,12,Fnever before, and it's almost entirely
OL,13,Faway from Labour and the Conservatives.
OL,15,FFor the first time, five or more
OL,16,Fparties are gaining a meaningful
OL,17,Famount of support in the polls. What
OL,18,Fis more, the election results
OL,19,Fthemselves could make this splintering
OL,20,Fmore likely.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FAnd yet, beneath this fragmentation,
OL,7,Fthe splintering of political support
OL,8,Fis anything but random; it is
OL,9,Fhappening within two clear political
OL,10,Fsides.
OL,12,FThe two graphs below take the same
OL,13,FYouGov data, but add the percentages
OL,14,Fof people who supported a party in the
OL,15,F'left bloc' (Labour, the Liberal
OL,16,FDemocrats, Greens, Plaid Cymru and the
OL,17,FSNP) or the 'right bloc'
OL,18,F(Conservatives and Reform UK) in 2024
OL,19,Fand this April.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
