PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FDespite increased switching, people
OL,7,Ftend to stay within ideological groups
OL,8,Fof parties:
OL,10,FThis is important for making sense of
OL,11,FBritish politics right now, and it's
OL,12,Fwhy the two main parties may be in
OL,13,Freal trouble come May 7.
OL,15,FIf party choice at the local level
OL,16,Fbecomes about backing the best-placed
OL,17,Fparty on one's own side to beat the
OL,18,Fother, different areas of the country
OL,19,Fmay, essentially, be swapping the
OL,20,Flocal dominant party on the left and
OL,21,Fthe local dominant party on the right.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FThis may leave Labour and the
OL,7,FConservatives in real trouble in areas
OL,8,Fwhere voters think other parties are
OL,9,Fbest placed to win. That's self-
OL,10,Fevident in Wales, where Reform seems
OL,11,Fto be replacing the Conservatives and
OL,12,FPlaid Cymru seems to be replacing
OL,13,FLabour. Repeated across the country,
OL,14,Fwe'd see a high level of fragmentation
OL,15,Fnationally and in English Councils,
OL,16,Fbut local choices boiling down to
OL,17,Fdifferent parties in each bloc.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FWhen we wake up on May 8 and 9, the
OL,7,Fresults may look like a patchwork
OL,8,Fquilt of different parties. But they
OL,9,Fwill still reflect the two-sided
OL,10,Fnature of British politics ` a left
OL,11,Fbloc and a right bloc ` but with
OL,12,FLabour and the Conservatives likely no
OL,13,Flonger the dominant party on either
OL,14,Fside. At least for now.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
