FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777741555
OL,3,CAre the May elections the beginning of
OL,4,Cthe end for the two big parties?
OL,6,FCritically, the results will help
OL,7,Finform future assessments of which
OL,8,Fparty in a voters' bloc is now the
OL,9,Fmost viable locally, and voters may
OL,10,Ffind it even harder to return to
OL,11,FLabour and the Conservatives in a
OL,12,Fgeneral election.
OL,14,FCould the two traditional parties ever
OL,15,Fregain their dominance? This will come
OL,16,Fdown to whether voters are turning
OL,17,Ftheir backs on the two traditional
OL,18,Fparties for good, or whether they
OL,19,Freturn to the familiar come the next
OL,20,Fgeneral election.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
